message:
Hi Stephen,

I have used task.run to execute the for loop. But it consumes more time than running the same code synchronously. Please find the code snippet from below.

private int max = 20000;
int max1 = 0;
  private async void UIJob_Click()
        {
            Stopwatch watch = new Stopwatch();
            watch.Start();
            await Task.Run(()=>SomeUIJob());
            watch.Stop();
            var secon = watch.Elapsed.TotalSeconds;
        }
 private void SomeUIJob()
        {
            for (int i = 0; i < max; i++)
            {
                if (i % 100 == 0) { Debug.WriteLine($"     UI time elapsed "); }
            }
        }

Can you please provide any suggestion to improve the performance while running the loop with task.run?
